<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08055e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08055e">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08055e"> 55(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> rusty pen ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Il y a des encres, notamment les encres bleues et rouges, qui s&apos;&eacute;talent, et des plumes rouill&eacute;es dont les becsne fonctionnent plus, en sorte que l&apos;&eacute;criture r&eacute;pond infid&egrave;lement &agrave; la pression de la main. <br><font color="green">[There are some inks, notably the blue and red, which spread out, as well as rusty pens with nibs that do not work anymore: the result is that the writing does not faithfully reflect the pressure of the hand.]</font> <small> J Cr&eacute;pieux-Jamin, <a name="JCJL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JCJL"><cite title="source">Les &eacute;l&eacute;ments de l'&eacute;criture des canailles</cite></a> (1923) 220</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
